Reasoning: The paper deals with nonmonotonic inference operations, which are a central topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also discusses properties of these operations that have been studied in the context of logic (cs.LO) and provides a characterization of right-absorbing and cumulative operations, which are relevant to complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses extending finitary operations to infinitary operations, which is a topic in programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper provides a generalization of the notion of compactness, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR).
